 </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">When you flip MBO - you can deploy proton torpedoes and your power at systems is +3.<br>
<br>
Start Aim High, Insight, Superficial Damage...this means you have some retrieval protection, you can run the proton engine, and you can grab honor.<br>
<br>
Flip ASAP and shuttle characters up to Yavin 4.  There is no reason to stay there, cuz you can&#146;t drain.<br>
<br>
HOTJedi will protect the yavin twix sites.  Even after HONOR is killed, this will still work.<br>
<br>
With Aim High and 2 starship weapons, you will be power +5.  With Concentrate all fire add +3 for each starfigther weapon firing.  So - two ships with 2 weapons firing is power +14.<br>
<br>
Add you forfeit those proton torpedoes and next turn you are deploying them from the reserve deck.<br>
<br>
You red/gold squadrons are deploy -2 to Yavin, which makes them useful in this deck.  The red squads also allow protons to fire for free (which may seems like nothing, but will help out)<br>
<br>
Bantha droid is sweet - no lateral damage ever.<br>
<br>
All pilots are intended to go on capitals, and keep the capitals around.<br>
<br>
This deck should win on space drains, with launching the assualt adding a sweet +1<br>
<br>
Need ideas for:<br>
protecting the ground based drains...maybe turn it into a hidden base deck with a portable scanner<br>
